        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 28 at 6:13PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 612 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
West Mountain, or near Gilmer, moving south at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Longview, Kilgore, White Oak, Gladewater, Clarksville City, East
Mountain, Liberty City, West Mountain, Lakeport, Union Grove, Warren
City, Rolling Meadows, and Judson.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
